				\begin{document}$$= \frac{{X_{{\mathrm{obs}}} - X_{{\mathrm{exp}}}}}{{StDev_{{\mathrm{exp}}}}}$$\end{document}=Xobs-XexpStDevexp; where Xobs is the metric of interest, Xexp is the mean value and StDevexp is the standard deviation from the null distribution. This is a standardisation that quantifies the position of the observed metric within the null distribution in terms of units of standard deviation55.
